                            <comment id="14567562" author="rohini" created="Mon, 1 Jun 2015 16:49:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So with this patch only in case of skewed outer join, the sample is also broadcast to the skewed join vertex. After 0.15, we need to revisit the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4377&quot; title=&quot;Skewed outer join produce wrong result if a key is oversampled&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4377&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4377&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to see if we can do it in a better way so that we still do dynamic parallelism for skewed outer join as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
